         <tr class=3D"replica" name=3D"s1">
          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Tomorrow, the Brook=
lyn Museum will announce <b>Melissa</b> <b>Joseph</b> as the winner of this=
 year=E2=80=99s Uovo prize, which recognizes the work of an emerging Brookl=
yn-based artist. The prize includes a solo presentation at the Brooklyn Mus=
eum, a commission for a 50-by-50-foot public art installation on Uovo=E2=80=
=99s Bushwick facility, and a $25,000 unrestricted cash grant. (Uovo, by th=
e way, specializes in storing and transporting art, wine, and other collect=
ibles.)<br/><br/>I spoke to the Brooklyn Museum=E2=80=99s director <b>Anne<=
/b> <b>Pasternak</b> and Uovo founder <b>Steven Guttman</b> about Joseph an=
d the prize. This interview has been lightly condensed and edited.<br/></td=
>
         </tr>
