          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><i>Pasternak</i>: I=
t=E2=80=99s a huge win. I really want to emphasize a point here, which is t=
hat lots of people love collecting young, emerging artists, but Steve talks=
 about really helping them and supporting them. He=E2=80=99s talking about =
not just buying their work, he actually hustles to help artists out. When w=
e were at Art Basel, he had recently fallen in love with a painter=E2=80=99=
s work from South Korea. He had books with him that he was giving to dealer=
s to try to help her out because she didn=E2=80=99t have gallery representa=
tion. I don=E2=80=99t know many people who do what Steve does. <br/><br/>Uo=
vo was opening a huge facility in Bushwick=E2=80=94and Steve knew that, of =
course, there are more artists of all disciplines living in Brooklyn than a=
nywhere else in the world. He has often acquired work by those artists and =
then shown it at Uovo. And then the fact that the
artists have a billboard in Bushwick=E2=80=94how many artists are going to =
have a giant mural anywhere, let alone in Bushwick, which is also a home to=
 so many artist=E2=80=99s studios? This is a real moment of pride for these=
 artists. <br/><br/><b>On an institutional level, what does the museum get =
out of identifying emerging artists? You also have <i>The Brooklyn Artists =
Exhibition</i> this year for the 200th anniversary of the museum, which als=
o emphasized emerging artists. </b><br/><br/><i>Pasternak</i>: Audiences to=
day want to see artists of their time. Artists today want to see artists of=
 their time. And I think we approach it with a historic lens, because we=E2=
=80=99re trying to identify young, emerging=E2=80=94I should say, <i>Brookl=
yn</i> artists=E2=80=94who we think have important things to say and who ar=
e adding to art history. That=E2=80=99s the job of the curators. That=E2=80=
=99s why we have the curators nominate artists that they=E2=80=99re keeping=
 an eye on, whose studios they=E2=80=99re going to, and then we take
a look together and decide whether we think they=E2=80=99re going to be abl=
e to pull off a really strong show. Though they may be young, we believe th=
at they=E2=80=99re going to be able to make a great mural. We think that th=
is is going to be really transformative for their practice. And we think th=
at their work is adding to the art-historical canon. <br/></td>
         </tr>
