ould mean to the community. Because I don=E2=80=99t think there=E2=80=99s a=
ny question, now that I look back at the five years we=E2=80=99ve been doin=
g this, that this has had a big impact on the art community in Brooklyn, an=
d maybe even all of New York.<br/><br/><i>Pasternak</i>: It=E2=80=99s had a=
n impact on the artists, themselves. <b>Baseera Khan</b> ended up having a =
show at the Hirshhorn. Her career completely changed. Museums started to bu=
y her work. The same was true for <b>John Edmonds</b>. Many of the artists =
have had skyrocketing careers. John got hired by all these major fashion ma=
gazines to do shoots. I mean, this was a guy
who didn=E2=80=99t have support before, so it was really game-changing for =
the artists involved.<br/><br/><b>How is the process run? How do you sift t=
hrough what are obviously a large number of artists? I know that you have f=
inalists=E2=80=94but you don=E2=80=99t announce them.</b><br/><br/><i>Paste=
rnak</i>: The curators come with a shortlist of about 25 or 30 artists, and=
